title: More rail delays after train breaks down
text:
0 comments 
COMMUTERS are facing delays in Southampton tonight after a train broke down. 
A First Great Western train has stopped near Sholing and is causing problems between Southampton Central and Fareham . 
Waits of up to 30 minutes are being reported. Share article 
National Rail says they expect problems to persist until 8pm tonight. 
It comes after a CrossCounty train derailed at Eastleigh this morning , causing long delays in the morning rush hour. Promoted Stories More rail delays after train breaks down   Keep in touch with local news
